PSD with solar photons is an important low-energy release process when sufficient UV flux is present and free Na or K is available on the surface. For Mercury and the Moon only Na and K have significant release rates due to PSD. The experimentally determined PSD cross-section for Na is Qi=(3±1)×10−20\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
