Whether flares at other stars are also often related with CMEs is yet a matter of debate, and they might at least be restricted for magnetically very active stars (e.g. Moschou et al. 2019). Stellar flares, however, can reach energies of up to more than 1030\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
