Model estimates of plasma impact fluxes on the surface are at the higher end of the observed range. Kallio and Janhunen (2003) used their hybrid model to simulate proton impact across Mercury’s entire surface for a wide range of solar wind conditions. They found ion fluxes impacting on the surface ranging 107\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
