				\begin{document}$$ \mathrm{H}+\mathrm{NaAl} \mathrm{Si}_{3} \mathrm{O}_{8} \rightarrow \mathrm{Na}+\mathrm{AlO}+3\mathrm{Si} \mathrm{O}_{2} + \mathrm{H}_{2} \mathrm{O} $$\end{document} again providing the atomic Na on the surface. Similarly, for potassium feldspar (orthoclase, KAl3Si3O8\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
